                            <comment id="13538149" author="shreejay" created="Fri, 21 Dec 2012 15:43:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The first box when highlighted shows the correct number. But due to the box not resizing the rest of the counts are wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13547142" author="elyograg" created="Tue, 8 Jan 2013 19:23:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still a problem as of branch_4x checked out yesterday.  Screenshot attached.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;solr-impl 4.1-SNAPSHOT 1429996 - ncindex - 2013-01-07 14:09:58&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13561154" author="steffkes" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2013 22:15:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=elyograg&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;elyograg&quot;&gt;elyograg&lt;/a&gt; would you mind attaching the output of &lt;tt&gt;/solr/inclive/admin/luke?wt=json&amp;amp;fl=catchall&lt;/tt&gt; ? that would be very helpful to get some realworld-data. perhaps we should also change the display of the histogram, because that doesn&apos;t like pretty good as well?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13561406" author="elyograg" created="Thu, 24 Jan 2013 04:07:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s the luke output you requested.  This is actually two complete responses - one for the inclive that you requested, and another for one of the large shards - s0live.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13562902" author="steffkes" created="Fri, 25 Jan 2013 18:46:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached Screenshot (schema-browser_histogram.png) shows how the new Histograms will look like, using Data from Shawn (the two on top) as well as exampedocs (the two at the bottom)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thoughts on this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13562954" author="hossman" created="Fri, 25 Jan 2013 19:44:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 ... nice.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Why are the numbers formated as &lt;tt&gt;8&apos;388&apos;608&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;8,388,608&lt;/tt&gt; or the more SI recomended &lt;tt&gt;8 388 608&lt;/tt&gt;?  is &lt;tt&gt;&quot;\&apos;&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; a locale based convention i&apos;m not aware of? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13562963" author="steffkes" created="Fri, 25 Jan 2013 19:53:38 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Why are the numbers formated as &lt;tt&gt;8&apos;388&apos;608&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;8,388,608&lt;/tt&gt; or the more SI recomended &lt;tt&gt;8 388 608&lt;/tt&gt;? is &lt;tt&gt;&quot;\&apos;&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; a locale based convention i&apos;m not aware of?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Uhm, that&apos;s a good question oO That&apos;s the same formatting rule i used for the DIH-Interface, grabbed a short Javascript-Snippet from StackOverflow which included this apostrophe. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If we change the formatting-character, i&apos;d like to use the , instead of the whitespace - because the whitespace only &quot;works well&quot; if you use mono-space formatting (as you did in your comment), otherwise the space between the digits is so small, that it does not really help while scanning the whole number.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;edit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;hmm, maybe .. looks, like it&apos;s the swiss formatting rule, but i didn&apos;t realize that &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/biggrin.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13562988" author="steffkes" created="Fri, 25 Jan 2013 20:20:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Instead of &quot;maybe&quot; .. have a look at your own .. the two samples on top are updated .. the first using whitespace and the second using comma as separator - let me know which one &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13563129" author="hossman" created="Fri, 25 Jan 2013 22:56:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, 16 years of education at US schools has biased me in favor of using comma as the thousand separator &amp;#8211; but i appreciate that people smarter then me clam whitespace separation is less confusing when communicating with people from other cultures that have diff conventions. (although i appreciate your point about it mainly being useful in fixed width fonts)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;truthfully i don&apos;t really care what we use: i was just surprised by the apostrophes since that&apos;s not a convention i&apos;d ever seen before in any locale.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
